{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205696386/1930092201/0286.xml":{"full_text":"2\nCHANG\u2019S TROOPS ENTER PEIPING WITHOUT FIRING SINGLE SHOT\nm is qoiei\nUH\nMILER\nNorthern Rebel Movement\nBelieved Definitely Ended;\nDeal Was Kept in Secret\nLONDON. Sept. 22 (INB.).\nPeiping, seat of the northern co\nalition which, for more than a\nyear, has opposed the nationalist\ngovernment at Nanking, coursed\nalong under a nep rule today, ac\ncording to a Daily Telegraph dis-,\npatch from .that important Chi\nnese center.\nThe city was occupied without\nthe firing of a single shot by the\ntroops of Marshal Chang Hsueh-\nLiang, the Mukden warlord. His\noccupational forces expected to\nenter the city of Tientsin before\nsunset, according to the Peiping\ndispatch.\nThe Mukden army moved in on\nthe heels of the forces of Gen.\nYen Hsl-Shan, head of the north\nern coalition who reportedly re\nsigned his post last week and an\nnounced he would retire with his\narmy into the mountainous Shansi\nterritory.\nBusiness As Usual\nApparently, a secret understand\ning existed between Yen and the\nMukden commander, as evacua\ntion proceeded in the most matter\nof-fact manner and without even\na show of hostilities. Foreigners\nand Chinese residents were unper\nturbed by the change in military\ngarrisons, pursuing business in the\nusual way.\nNanking, according to informa\ntion, celebrated the occupation\nof Peiping as the final indication\nthat the northern rebel move\nment was definitely ended. Both\nthe Nationalist government and\nGeneral Yen Hsi-Shan carried on\nstrenuous negotiations during\nthe year bargaining for the sup\nport of the Manchurian war lord\nInformed Chinese circles\npointed out, however, that\nChang\u2019s real purpose in occupy\ning the northern cities in the\nwake of Yen\u2019s evacuation has\nnot as yet been disclosed. It is\nsupposed that he is anxious to\nsecure the revenues of the sur\nrounding territory and obtain\npolitical posts for his lieutenants.\nFean Communism\nBoth President Chiang Kai-\nShek of the Nationalist regime\nand Marshal Chang Hsueh-Liang\nhave been vociferous in urging\nearly cessation of military cam\npaigns, stressing the dire eco\nnomic exigencies.\nIn addition, the spectre of\nCommunism and Russian aggres\nsion was believed to have given\nan added incentive to the peace\nefforts of the leaders of the vari\nous factions.\nAdvices from Nanking indi\ncated further, also, that the Muk\nden war lord may have arranged\nwith the rebel commander to\nwithdraw peaceably in order to\nretain him as a possible ally in\nenforcing upon Nanking various\npolicy and administration changes.\nIn order to assure an early\ncomplete understanding between\nthe Northerners and Nationalists,\nMarshal Chang is expected to ex\ntend his influence along the\nnorthern Shantung-Tsinan Kaio\nchau railroad.\nSHANGHAI, Sept. 22 (1.N.5.).\nOn the eve of victory over the\nNorthern rebel coalition Tan\nYen-Kai, president of the execu\ntive council of the Nationalist\ngovernment, died at Nanking to\nday.\nDeath was caused by a blood\ndot, according to the report.\nJONESTEES OFF\nFOR RECORD\nf Continued Front Pago 1)\non at the end of the qualifying\nround and even Jones himself, al\nways the last man to admit that\nthe future is settled, will admit\nthat he will qualify.\nAs a matter of fact, he will\nhave a hard time avoiding the\nqualifying medal, which is one of\nthe things he doesn\u2019t want. An\nother is a meeting with a reso\nlute opponent in either of the\ntwo 18-hole match play rounds\nthat will follow on Wednesday.\nThese rounds are Jones\u2019 bete noir,\nif you follow my French or even\nif you don\u2019t. He almost lost here\nin 1926. He almost lost again in\n1927. He repeated in 1928 and,\nfinally, in 1929 he succeeded ad\nmirably, thanks to the courageous\nefforts of Goodman.\nFor -purposes of the record, to\nday's round opened at 8 a. m.\nJones started with Emery Strat\nton at 9:19, with Sweetser going\nat 10:05, Marston at, 10:15, Oui\nmet at 10:35, Tolley at 11, John\nson at 12:35, Voigt at 1:05, Von\nEm at 1:20, Goodman at 1:25,\nWilling at 1:50 and Evans at\n1:10.\nIf you r\u00bbhi\u00ab time. It by tecatiac\ntai Mad* thraash the Clawi-\nI World\u2019s Beautiful\nr T .3r 'T -t 'J\n.1 d J\"' I\nnF\nB 1 I'\nvc Arie*\nBi wik-\na B Jl\nShl sH\n\u25a0r s\n\u2014lnternational Newzreel\nFERNANDA GONCALVES YOLANDA PEREIRA\nBRAZIL PREFERS brunettes, regardless of gentlemen\u2019s preferences. Miss Yo\nlanda Pereira was recently crowned \u201cMiss Universe\u201d at the annual bathing beauty\ncontest in Rio de Janeiro. Fernando Goncalves, \u201cMiss Portugal,\u201d was awarded\nsecond place.\n]R\\DDOCKPICie ES\nJ\n(Continual Front Pogo 1)\nSECOND RACE\u2014Six furlongz. Puree, IL2M. Claiming Three-year-olda\nPP HORSE WOT ODDS JOCKEY COMMENT\n4 Ultimata Vote 194 4-1 A. PanSariraaa Ready for nueztlon\n5 Jamas M 1\u00ab4 1-1 G. Depeao In \u00abood condition\nIt Bustling 194 11-1 E. James Has worked well\n19 Elstar 191 19-1 R. Flnn9rty Ready for beet\n1 Starference 1\u00ab4 15-1 No boy The Bleeper in here\n2 Bunyora 194 14-1 P. Mulrooney In touch sodt\n7 Annedire 199 15-1 No boy Up against it here\nS Gracious Me 199 14-1 C. Landolt Been racing poorly\n12 Sun Bonita 104 12-1 L. Aron Has early speed\n13 Xelly\u2019e Pride I*l 11-1 A. Richard Some races fair\nMizzou IR-1 w Nelson Up against it hers\n3 Jovial Friar 194 14-1 No boy Prefers soft: track\nSCRATCHED\u2014-Eight O' Four, willing, Escondida. Silver Cord, Shasta Ftar.\nRuddy Sir.\nTHIRD RACE\u2014Six furlongs. Purse. *1,299. Claiming. Two-year-olds.\nPP HORSE WGT ODDS JOCKEY COMMENT\nTwill 104 4-1 r. Finnerty %-ratched for this\n4 Fond 103 4-1 O. Boucher One to lick\n3 Nadia 107 7-1 H. West Improved: watch\n2 Gypsie Chief 103 7-1 E. James Fit and ready\n10 Nervator 1\u00ab\u00ab \u00bb-l D. Bubols In good condition\n11 Brown Hill 1\u00abS 7-1 R. Finnerty Might take it all\n4 Burnam 105 12-1 D. Bryant Rome races