D\u2014Sunstroke, Boyish Bob, Hedendeen, Fortunes Favorite, Jeu\n4e Bar. HMHTMhfFnA\nSEVENTH RACE\u2014One and one-eighth miles. Purse. *1,300. Claiming. Three\nyear-olds and upward.\nPP JIORSE WGT ODDS JOCKEY COMMENT\n7 Graydale 107 7-1 E. McLaughlin Been hiding; beat\n4 Spanish Aater 104 5-1 T. Boucher Haa worked well\n3 Quibbler 107 9-1 A. Richard Fresh and good\n9 Sweet Mandy 194 4-1 H. R. Riley In good condition\n9, Jodhpur 10.1 7-1 W. Jvhna The sleeper io here\n1 Try Again 107 15-1 C. Grbsa In tough spot\n4 Col. crump 103 12-1 O. Laidley Noeda mud for best\nSmiling Betty 109 12-I A. Pondergraea Better than rated\n10 Forbec in i\u00ab-i No boy Up against It hero\n11 Mine Maryland 10* I|-1 E. Jamoa Laat very bad\n13 Pat Field .....f...... 197 11-l T. Vercher Been raelng badly\nl\u00bb-l D I\u00bb\u201cl>oia_ Not much chance\nSCRATCHED\u2014PrickIy Heat. Aviator, Peter, Mao Fogle, Gotham, Col. Board.\nBEST BET\u2014STOCK MARKET.\n\nBURNING TRUCK\nBLOCKS BRAD\nBOYCE, Va., Sept. 22.\u2014Traffic\non the State Highway through\nBoyce was tied up for more than\nhalf an hour last night by a\nburning truck which ignited\nbrush at the side of the road,\ncausing a brush fire.\nThe truck, loaded with 93 bags\nof white potatoes and 11 barrels\nof sweet potatoes, valued at S3BO,\nwas en\u2019 route to Winchester. The\nvehicle and load were owned by\nH. T. Bell, of Cape Charles, Va..\nwhile H. W. Francis was driving\nthe truck.\nFrancis had stopped at a fill\ning station just east of Boyce to\nfill his gasoline tank and was run\nning down a slight incline into\nthe town when the overflowing\ntank was ignited either by a\nspark from the brakes or by a\nbackfire. The tank exploded,\nthrowing burning gasoline over\nthe truck and its load. Bell es\ncaped unhurt, but Francis was\nslightly burned.\nBoth the truck and load were\ndestroyed.\nTHB WASHINGTON TIMBS\nWALES MAY BE\nGODFATHER\nGLAMIS, Ecotland, Sept. 22\n(U.S.).\u2014The Duchess of York\u2019s\nbaby will shortly be christened\nat a very quiet ceremony in the\nprivate chapel of Glamis Castle.\nIt is practically certain that\nonly two or three Christian\nnames will be bestowed. \u201cJean\u201d\nand \u201cMargaret\u201d are favored on\nthe Glamis countryside.\nA report declares that the\nPrince of Wales will act as god\nfather, while the godmothers will\ninclude the Duchess* sister, Lady\nElphinstone. The King and Queen\nwill, of course, be present.\nThe font will contain Jordan\nbaptismal water, such as was\nused at Princess Elizabeth\u2019s chris\ntening. Observed also will be the\nancient custom of sprinkling\nsweet-smelling herbs around the\nfont\u2014a relic of the days when\nsuch precautions against plague\nwere regarded as essential.\nAt the conclusion of the cere\nmony the Duke of York will be\npresented with a purse contain\ning five gold sovereigns\nBAN FDR GRAIN\nDEALS SEEN\n(Continuoi Front Pago 1)\nsian account. Secretary of Agri\nculture Hyde charged that the\nbrokers had handled selling orders\nfor 5,000,000 bushels of wheat tor\nfuture deliveries for the All-Rus\nsian Textile Syndicate, a subsidi\nary of the Soviet Amtorg Trading\nCorporation, government organi\nsation. He said the Russians\nnever intended to import wheat\nfrom Russia to fill these selling\norders but hoped merely to smash\ndown wheat prices in this coun\ntry, later buying enough gra\u2019n\nhere at lower prices to fill the\norders.\nThe Administration was inter\nested in possible action by the\nBoard of Trade. Hyde has al\nleady pointed out to John A.\nBunnell, board president, that\nthe law compels it to make\nregulations to prpvide for the pre\nvention of manipulation of prices.\nHe has told Bunnell that the\nRussian transactions were made\nsolely to manipulate prices in de\nfiance of the law.\nMight Close Exchange\nIf the Chicago authorities fail\nto take any action, the Govern\nment undoubtedly will move. For\none thing, Federal action might\nbe initiated against the brokers,\ncharging them with speculation\nin grain or with a conspiracy\nto depress prices in violation of\nthe antitrust laws.\nAnd if the situation developed\nan agricultural emergency, the\nexchanges themselves could be\nclosed. At present, no such ac\ntion is contemplated but the\npower to close exchanges gives\nthe Government a tremendous\nweapon.\nBoard of Trade Group\nOpens Investigation\nCHICAGO, Sept. 22 (1.N.5.).\nIn response to charges made by\nSecretary of Agriculture. Hyde,\nthe business conduct committee\nof the Chicago Board of Trade\ntoday undertook a \u201cthorough\" in\nvestigation of purported opera\ntions of Russian grain trading\noperatives on the Chicago Ex\nchange.\nJoseph Badenoch, chairman of\nthe committee, announced that\nhis group will begin a direful in\nquiry regarding operations of the\nAll Russian Textile Syndicate of\nNew York. Badenoch said his\ncommittee\u2019s findings would be an\nnounced after today\u2019s sessions,\nadding that the matter had been\nunder consideration for ten days.\nMembers of the Exchange, in\nexpressing their opinions, said\ninasmuch as the grain markets\nare open to the world the govern\nment should not place the re\nsponsibility tn the Soviet situa\ntion on the Exchange.\nLURAY LEAGUE ELECTS\nLURAY, Va., Sept. 22.\u2014The Lu\nray Civic League has re-elected\nthe following officers:\nMrs. W. C. Lauck, president;\nMrs. T. G. Hamilton and Mrs. C.\nG* Bailey, vice presidents; Mrs.\nFrances Sale, treasurer. Miss An\nnie Pierce declined re-election as\nsecretary and was succeeded by\nMrs. A. C. Brubaker.\nGAS PARLEY SEPT. 29\nROCKVILLE, Md., Sept. 22.\nRepresentatives of the Washing\nton Gas Light Company will meet\nwith the town council next Mon\nday night to discuss the bringing\nof gas into Rockville.\nTho ffoHonat DoF,\nHITLER PUTSCH\nSTILL FEARED\nIN BERLIN\n1 W 1\nPlan Is Denied by New Chief\nAnd Premier Scouts Danger,\nBut Public Is Expectant\nBERLIN, Sept. 22 (INB.).\u2014X\nweek and a day after Germany\u2019s\nstartling elections, which en\ndowed the Fascists with minority\nleadership in the forthcoming\nReichstag, the nation remained\ncalm but shaken and extremely\nnervous.\nIn an air surcharged with po\nlitical tensity, rumbling with dis\ncordant party clamor and the oc\ncasionally ribald shouts of dis\norderly radical elements, lowered\nthe ever-threatening cloud of a\npossible Fascist \u201cputsch.\" Ber\nliners especially attended to their\nroutine tasks with the momentary\nexpectation of hearing the roll of\ndrumfire tnd the announcement\nthat the Fascists\u2019 \u201cMarch to Ber\nlin\" has begun.\nGovernment Confident\nEver since the vote count lifted\nmilitant and colorful Adolf Hitler\nfrom the ranks of the ordinary\nagitator to a dictatorial political\nposition by virtue of the 107 seats\nhis national Socialists (Fascists)-\ncaptured a week ago, predictions\nhave run rife that the \u201cLittle\nMussolini\u201d soon would rush his\npaid \u201cstorm troops\u201d against the\nincumbent government in an ef\nfort to raise the standards of\nfascism above Wllhelmstrasse.\nChancellor Heinrich Bruening,\nhead of the Hindenburg cabinet,\nconfident that the army is loyal,\ncontinued today to minimize the\ndanger, while Minister of War\nGroener assured the apprehensive\nthat any attempted revolution\nwould be quickly squelched.\nAlthough the Hitlerites have\nclamored ceaselessly for repre\nsentation in the ministry and a\nleading voice in the government.\nBruening so far has given small\nindication that he will compro\nmise with the extremist elements\nunless forced.\nJ Plans Old CabtaH\nHe has announced he will sub\nmit the same cabinet rtow in\npower to the new Reichstag Which,\nassembles next month. His prob\ni able intentions, unless forced out\ni of office at the opening sessions\nof Parliament, will be to join\nforces with the powerful Socialists\ni under Premier Otto Braun, of\nPrussia, in formation of a \u201cgrand\ncoalition\" in opposition to the ex\ntremlst blocs.\nHerr Hitler himself, scouting\nrumors that he is planning a Fas\ncist putsch and blamipg Commu\ni nists with disseminating them to\ndiscredit his party, asesrted he\ndid not need to make a putsch to\ngain control of the government.\nGRAFT FAMILY\nID BE QUIZZED\nAUGUSTA, Me., Sept. 22 (I.N.\nS.).\u2014ln an effort to find out if\nany members of the Crater house\nhold know anything of the strange\ndisappearance of Justice Joseph\nF. Crater, of 1 New York, county\nAttorney Frank E. Southard, of\nKennebec county, today moved to\nquestion Mrs. Crater and several\nemployes.\nHe said he would send Capt. Jo\nseph F. Young, jr\u201e of the Maine\nState police, to the Crater summer\ncamp at Belgrade Lakes today to\nquestion the missing jurist\u2019s wife;\nher mother, Mrs. F. W. Wheeler;\ntheir chauffeur, Fred Kohler, and\nMargaret Lynch, maid.\nSouthard said the questioning\nis at request of Thomas C. T,\nCrain, district attorney of New\nYork. Southard said if Mrs.\nCrater and others refused to talk\nto Young, it was possible she and\nher servants would be called be\nfore'the county grand jury here\nnext week.\nThe attorney said District At\ntorney Crain wrote:\n\u201cSome of Judge Crateris\nfriends and associates think he\nhad been the victim of fool\nplay and possibly of some crime\nin your jurisdiction.\u201d\nThis was the first time it has\nbeen intimated that Judge Crater,\nwho disappeared on August 8,\nmay have met his death in this\ncounty, of which Belgrade Lakes,\nwhere the Crater summer home\nis located, is a part.\nIt was considered likely that\nstate police may search the Cra\nter summer home and possibly\ndrag Great Pond, a body of wa\nter near the home, for the body\nof the missing jurist.\nkilled\nENGLEWOOD, N. J., Sept. 22\n(INB.). \u2014Investigators today said\nthat Jack H. G. Mills, Jr., stu\ndent flyer killed in a crash Sun\nday, may have fainted and lost\ncontrol of his ol\u00bbn\u00ab- No attempt\nto use a parachute wm made by\nthe pilot as his ship went into a\nf dive.\nMONDAY, BEFTEMBEN T*\u00aeO\nQuite Films for Flying\nu J\nf I A\n\u25a0W J\nA ml\nI\n\u2014lnternational Newzreel\nEDNA MAE COOPER\nAFTER CRASHING the gates of filmland, Mae,\nCooper, of Los Angeles, suddenly deserted the screen\nto take up aviation, because she considers it to offer a\ngreater field for the future. She is now studying to\nbecome a commercial pilot\n'LEGS' DIAMOND\nLANDS TODAY\nPHILADELPHIA, Sept. 22\n(INB.).\u2014Accompanied by a opat\nload of canaries, Jack (Legs) Dia\nmond, New York racketeer, was\nscheduled to arrive here today\nfrom Germany. He sailed from\nHamburg September 8 on the\nfreighter Hanover, after being re\n2uested to embark by German\nuthorities.\nDiamond may decide not to get\noff the boat and go on to Balti\nmore, where it was reported his\nwife was waiting to meet him.\nShould he land here police may\ntake him into custody although it\nwas denied New York authorities\nhad asked them to hold him\nhere.\nAt police headquarters it was\nsaid Diamond might be taken\ninto custody until it is definitely\nestablished whether New York\nauthorities wanted him and if\nthey did not he would be invited\nto leave Philadelphia at once.\nCLUB PICKS HEADS\nLEESBURG, Va.. Sept. 22.\u2014The\nAldie Home Demonstration Club\nwas organized recently with the\nfollowing officers: Miss Katherine\nDougless, president; Mrs. Effie\nGrehan, vice president: Mrs. T. F.\nTyler, secretary-treasurer; Mrs.\nW. T. Carter, reporter. Hie club\nhas a membership of twelve.\n1,500 Years Old\nv ii\n\u2014lnternational Newsreel\nRUTH GEIGER\nTHESE ORNAMENTS worn\nby Miss Ruth Geiger. *t the\nexhibit of primitive Mexican\nart at Chicago, are more than\n1,500 years old. They are made\nof uncut diamonds and more\nthan 1,000 unfinished pearls.\nTARIFF HALTING\nTRADE PICKUP\nInflicting a very heavy blow on\nAmerica\u2019s foreign trade, the IL\n-0T0,000,000 Hawley-Smoot tariff\nact is delaying recovery of busi\nness, Representative John N. Gar\nner (D.), of Texas, declared yes\nterday.\nGamer. minority- leader of the\nHouse, and ranking Democrat on\nthe House Ways and Means Com\nmittee. which originated the tar\niff bill, said:\n\u201cThe extortions of the Grun\ndy tariff act amount to more\nin dollars and distress than\nthe steps taken to ameliorate\nthe suffering consequent on the\nHoover panic sum up in dollars\nand relief.\u201d\nPassing Phase\n\u201cThe misery of the panic is\na passing phase; ultimately the\nwounds of the economic disaster\nwill be healed. But the extor\ntions of the tariff Mil must con\ntinue until the Government\npasses into the hands other than\nthose that inflicted the injury to\nthe public welfare.\n\u201cMoreover, the Grandy tariff\nwin delay surcease from the\nindustrial agony, for it has in\nflicted a deadly blow on our\nforeign trade and until this is\ncured there is no possibility of\nseeing our mills and factories\nagain running at fuU capacity.\n\u201cThe exorbitant rates of\nthis MH have resulted in the\nimposition of reprisal duties by\nnumerous foreign countries,\namong them Canada, which\nhas been our best customer.\n\u201cThe tariff was enacted with\nthe single purpose of obtaining\na larger price from every item\non which the rate was changed,\nfrom applesauce to sine.\n\u201cIt is no answer to the bil\nlion-dollar extortion that pres\nent prices of. commodities have\nnot increased The present\nprices give us no index.\n\u201cThey are part of the gen\neral business depression. Inev\nitably they wiH rise when busi\nness is again normal.\nWAGES TOO LOW\nNEW YORK, Sept. 22 (1.N8.).\nEngland is suffering from too\nlow wages, according to Dr. John\nRobert Gregg, inventdr of a short\nhand system, who was in New\nYork today after a visit abroad.\nHigher wages will end England\u2019s\nperiod of depression and solve her\neconomic troubles, he said.\nEdison, Air-Minded,\nPays Two Visits\nTo Flying Field\nNEWARK, N. J., Sept. 22\n(IN.S.).\u2014Thomas A. Edison\nmay become deeply Interested\nin aviation, it was indicated to\nday. Por the second time in\nless than a week he visited\nan airport here Sunday and\nwatched planes soar over the\nfield.\nHe was much impressed by\nan autogyro, which speeds\nstraight up and down.\n\u201cThat\u2019s the ahswer, vthat\u2019s\nthe answer,\u201d he exclaimed after\nhe had watched the machine\ntake off vertically, speed up to\n115 miles an hour and then\nsettle slowly to earth without\nrolling.\nTREASURY MUST\nSHIFT POLICY\nOH ADD TAX\nAvailable Data Show 1 Per\nCent Slash Cannot Be Con\ntinued Without Big Loan\nWith date now available Indi\nrating to a practical certainty\nthe volume of Government re\nceipts up to the first of Janu\nary-before which time Secretary\nMellon must recommend to Con\ngress as to the continuation of\nthe 1 per cent tax reduction\u2014it\nappeared today that such a cut\ncould not be approved without a\ndecided upset in fiscal policies.\nNotwithstanding the fact that\nthe Administration through state\nments from the White House\nand Secretary Mellon virtually\nstand comltteed to a continua\ntion of the 1 per cent lower tax\non corporations and individual\nnormal incomes, it is now recog\nnized that conditions in Novem\nber and December may necessi\ntate a change in this attitude.\nAn official said:\nPoHcy May Be Changed\n\u201cOs course there can be a\ncontinuation of the 1 per exit\ntax cut providede there is a\nradical change in Treasury\npolicies. That, however, would\nset a bad precedent and it\nmight necessitate extraordinary\nborowing that would be un\neconomical to the Government,\nand indirect// without tavor\nable reaction on the public.\nWith the year practically three\nquarters gone and Federal Re\nserve Board and other compila\ntions from official sources show\ning that trade and industrial ac\ntivity has declined substantially\nfrom 1929, it appeared certain\nthe Government\u2019s income from\ncorporation and Individual taxes\nwould be cut materially.\nThe exact volume of the reduc\ntion cannot be told until the\nincome tax returns filed March\n15 are tabulated. These returns\nwill reflect incomes of the\ncalendar year 1930. The recom\nmendation to Congress relative to\nthe tax cut must be made before\nthe March returns are available\nfor examination.\nDuring Mellon\u2019s regime as Secre\ntary of the Treasury there here\ntofore has been a policy of con\nservatism as to estimates of re\nvenue and as to tax cutting. Not\nsince he entered office has there\nbeen such a difficult task in\nestimating revenue as presents\nitself for the last half of the\n1931 fiscal year.\nFear Political Effect\nThe one per cent tax reduc\ntion was recommended last year\nin order to give the taxpayers\nadvantage of an excess of receipts\nover the Governmental require\nments. Its proponents pointed\nout that such a policy would give\nthe taxpayers advantage of any\ntemporary surplus in the hands\nof the Treasury and would permit\nreturn to the permanent rates\nshould conditions necessitate. For\nthis reason they took the attitude\nthat a return to the 1928 revenue\nact rates is entirely justified be\ncause of the business depression.\nEvidently some Administration\nauthorities fear that the return\nto the 1928 rates would have an\nadverse political and economic\neffect.\nHUDMDGE\nDIVE FATAL\nNEW YORK, Sept. 22 (U.S.).\nAs several thousand motorists\nand pedestrians watched, Norman\nJ. Terry, professional stunt man,\ndived 213 feet today from the\nspan of the new Hudson River\nBridge, paying for his daring\nwith death.\nIt was believed to be a pub\nlicity stunt staged by a news\npaper and a movie concern.\nWort Bathing Suit\nTerry gained entrance to the\nclosely guarded approach to the\nbridge in a manner not yet de\ntermined by police.\nHe was clad in a bathing suit,\na pair of trousers and gymna\nsium shoes. He had fastened a\ntight corset around his body to\nprotect his ribs and a wooden\nbrace extended down his back.\nHis legs and arms were wrapped\nin gauze that was fastened by\nadhesive tape.\nv Motorists Watch\nTerry, who was 25 years old\nand lived in Kittanning, Pa.?\nedged his way along the narrow\ncat walk that runs besides the\ncables, at a dizzy height above\nthe water He was observed by\nseveral thousand motorists and\npedestrians on both sides of the\nriver who stopped to watch.\nHe stopped before he got to\nthe middle of the span and stood\npoised for a moment on the wire\ncable.\nThen he leaped into the river.\nTerry\u2019s failure to strike the water\nhead foremost is believed to have\ncaused his death. He was dead\nwhen taken from the water","height":"30441","width":"24023"}}
